				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Everyone:<BR>
<BR>
Lottery ticket sales will resume on Monday, May 21st. I'll be out of town until then. As of now there are 5290 ticket numbers issued, of which about 4400 were revenue generating.<BR>
<BR>
I am now increasing the amount that I personally guarantee from 5,000pp to 10,000pp. What this means is that on the day of the drawing if the net ticket revenue isn't at least 10,000pp...I will pay the difference personally. In other words you can be confident that at least 10,000pp will be paid to the 1st, 2nd and 3rd place winners.<BR>
<BR>
But please do not forget that I will soon begin accepting donated loot items. If you would care to donate then please give me a tell ingame. Only loot items valued at 250pp or greater will be accepted.<BR>
<BR>
I would also like to encourage Guilds to donate items in the name of their guild. My idea is to have a representative of each guild present at the drawing to actually hold the item they are donating and then hand it over to the winner. That was the guilds can take some credit for their contributions and also it will make the lottery drawing run faster and more smoothly.<BR>
<BR>
Look for this thread to be moved to the &quot;Quellious&quot; board here on Everlore very soon. I will also make similar threads on some of the top EQ boards on other websites. Thanks.<BR>
<BR>
Morthan Anuff<BR>
35th Level Druid<BR>
Greater Druids
