	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Dinadal:<BR>
<BR>
I have reread all of my posts and nowhere have I tried to declare myself as the &quot;originator&quot; of the Everquest Lottery. In addition, nowhere in my posts have I tried to dictate that other players interested in running their own lotteries must ask me for permission.<BR>
<BR>
I am one of 350,000+ players of Everquest. I would never be so arrogant as to think that administering a few player events would give me any sort of priveledged status.<BR>
<BR>
Please reread my posts and point out where I have voiced either of your claims. I will definitely apologize to you and all others if I have done anything of the sort.<BR>
<BR>
Now, onto both issues you mention:<BR>
<BR>
1. Am I the first person to do lotteries?<BR>
<BR>
I could care less about being the first in anything. My goal is to be the best I can be. This included running a well organized player event that maximizes all participants enjoyment, while maintaining a strict code of ethics.<BR>
<BR>
I think my lotteries have done just that. Of all the servers I have played on I have never seen anyone else run a better or more successful lottery than me. Thats my pride...nothing more.<BR>
<BR>
2. Do people have to ask me for permission to run a lottery?<BR>
<BR>
I think I answered this is my first paragraph, but I will elaborate. Whenever I run lotteries I have dozens of people asking me for the specific details of how I make the whole event so successful. Well, in the online world of anonymity...I have no idea about the true motives of these questions.<BR>
<BR>
Maybe someone wants to mirror my lottery and then run away with tons of money. How can I know? I can't. So I need to refrain from providing the intricate details, just to prevent this sort of thing from happening. <BR>
<BR>
These posts you are reading right now provide ample information for a bright person to duplicate or create a lottery. I just don't want to be responsible for another person screwing over their whole server. Make sense?<BR>
<BR>
So, I am simply saying that I am not willing to teach complete strangers how to scam several thousand other complete strangers. The only thing I can control are my own actions, and I do so by running damn good (and honest) player lotteries.<BR>
<BR>
Lottery Update:<BR>
<BR>
4028 Ticket Numbers Issued<BR>
<BR>
_____________________________________________<BR>
<BR>
Axhelm:<BR>
<BR>
Dinadal interpreted my words as me trying to either give permission or deny permission to you and others on the lottery issue. I want it clear that I have no desire to come across as being &quot;in charge&quot; of lotteries...in case you interpreted my words similarly.<BR>
<BR>
My suggestion to you is to run a lottery and do it well. If you prove yourself to the players on your server then future events will be easier to get up and running.<BR>
<BR>
I cannot help you as I don't know you. Even though you sound like you have good intentions, that could very well be a front to a major scam.<BR>
<BR>
I will say this. On your &quot;News&quot; post you have some minor mistakes. You are offering a quantity discount, but then your math doesn't add up.<BR>
<BR>
If 100 tickets cost 180pp, as opposed to 200pp then this is definetly a discount. The problem comes on your price break at a qty. of 100 tickets. You say 200 tickets = 370pp.<BR>
<BR>
If 100 tickets = 180pp, then 2 transactions of 100 tickets would cost 360pp total. Your price of 370pp means it is more economical to buy 100 tickets at a time. There is no real break. Make sense?<BR>
<BR>
Good luck...but you are on your own...by necessity. From your post it sounds like you have a pretty nice plan. It should work fine.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Morthan Anuff<BR>
35th Season Druid<BR>
Greater Druids
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
