	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Mr. Anonymous:<BR>
<BR>
The deal is &quot;Buy 5 Get 1 FREE,&quot; but not everyone takes advantage of the opportunity. Many people buy less than 5 and never get the FREE ticket. Many people buy a block of tickets this isn't a factor of 5, and therefore miss out on at least 1 FREE ticket.<BR>
<BR>
It is important to understand the terms I am using. &quot;Ticket numbers issued&quot; means exactly that...the last ticket issued will be the high-end of the /random draw range. If 10,000 total tickets were issued, then the number 10,000 will be used as the high-end of the range:<BR>
<BR>
/random 10,000<BR>
<BR>
The above random roll will produce a number between 1 and 10,000. Every single ticket number is unique and held by one person only. Even if many tickets (FREE) were not revenue generating, they are still held by players and are just as valid as revenue generating tickets. Players earned the right to have an extra ticket by buying 5 tickets or more, and thereby increasing the jackpot for all players.<BR>
<BR>
So, if 10,000 ticket numbers were issued...I must now deduct all of the FREE tickets when calculating gross ticket revenue. The FREE tickets are valid, but they do not contribute towards the jackpot.<BR>
<BR>
It so happens that of all the ticket numbers issued as of 5-15-01, about 16% were non-revenue generating. This percentage can only be equal to or less than 20%, and at this point can only be less than 20% seeing as so many people have bought quantities that didn't qualify for FREE tickets.<BR>
<BR>
I hope this made sense!<BR>
<BR>
__________________<BR>
<BR>
To the person asking exactly how I run these lotteries...I do not feel comfortable providing anymore information than I have already provided. There is too much risk in some screwball duplicating my lottery style and cheating their entire server out of money.<BR>
<BR>
I have to endure /shouts from plenty of skeptics everyday. Let me assure you...it takes alot to build a reputation where the entire server feels safe handing you money for nothing more than &quot;unique numbers.&quot; These lottos are exhausting, and I only do a few per year.<BR>
<BR>
My fear is teaching some unethical people how to efficiently cheat their fellow players. I don't want to do anything that will increase the already high level of distrust that exists in EQ. <BR>
<BR>
I have shared a great deal, but have refrained from including the &quot;sales&quot; and logistics aspect, which I believe are the most crucial elements of the lottery.<BR>
<BR>
I think player run events are awesome and I wish more people would get involved in this sort of thing. Doing a lottery is one of the more difficult projects, so why not think of some other great ideas?<BR>
<BR>
Maybe a huge party in the Arena in Lake Rathe?<BR>
<BR>
Maybe a biatholon in Oasis where players start on the dock and swim the length of the zone, then run up on shore. They would have to circle the zone and go around checkpoints at each corner where a player would sit and verify.  They could not use SoW or Lev...so MOBS would have to be avoided. Entry into the race would be 10pp per player, and everyone would have to be in a given level range. The winner takes 70%, 2nd place takes 20%, and 3rd takes 10%.<BR>
<BR>
Get creative...and make something happen...<BR>
<BR>
Morthan Anuff<BR>
35th Season Druid<BR>
Greater Druids
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
